CatDescriptText: Mr. Russell Harley, 3025 Centre Avenue, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 16, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "Do you think that Negroes are giving sufficient financial help to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People?" Answer reads: "No. The people in Pittsburgh don't believe in giving."
